function atan2(xx)

return atan(xx) +pi
    else

    end
end




function beta(lam,beta0)
    
return -atan2(1/(1/2*(-3*lam-2*1/tan(beta0)) ))
end


function x(lam, x0)
beta0=Beta0(x0)
return (x0*(4+9*lam^2 + 12*lam*1/tan(beta0) +4*1/(tan(beta0))^2  )^(1/3))/(2^(2/3) * (1+ 1/(tan(beta0))^2 )^(1/3) )
end

function t(lam)
return gamma*sqrt(delta)*lam
end

function lambda(t)
return t/(gamma*sqrt(delta))
end

function szift(lam, x0)
return -x(lam,x0)/(gamma*sqrt(delta))*sin(beta(lam,Beta0(x0)))*cos(beta(lam,Beta0(x0)))
end

^ 2) + 36 * pi * G * delta * lam * rho0 * x0 * gamma1 ^ 2 * rr ^ 2 + -18 * G * delta * lam * rho0 * sqrt(2) * pi ^ (3//2) * gamma1 ^ 2 * rr ^ 3 * erf((1 / 2) * x0 * sqrt(2) * rr ^ -1) * exp((1 / 2) * rr ^ -2 * x0 ^ 2)) * exp(-5//12 * rr ^ -2 * x0 ^ 2))
return real(ret)    
end

using DifferentialEquations
xpoczU=10


function rozwiazanie(s1,lamstar)

if s1<0    
    
function calyproblem(du, u, p, s)
du[1] = -derxpox0(u[1], u[2])
du[2] = -gamma*sqrt(delta)
du[3] = u[3]*derxpox0polam(u[1], u[2])
end


        
        
u0 = [lamstar; xpoczU; -1]

sspan=(0,-s1 ) ## 0 20

prob3 = ODEProblem(calyproblem, u0, sspan, abstol = 1e-5, reltol = 1e-5)
sol3 = solve(prob3)

return sol3(-s1)
        
    elseif s1>=0        
        
function calyproblem2(du, u, p, s)
du[1] = derxpox0(u[1], u[2])
du[2] = gamma*sqrt(delta)
du[3] = -u[3]*derxpox0polam(u[1], u[2])
end

u02 = [lamstar; xpoczU; -1]

sspan2=(0,s1 )  ### 0 60

prob32 = ODEProblem(calyproblem2, u02, sspan2, abstol = 1e-5, reltol = 1e-5)
sol32 = solve(prob32)

return sol32(s1)        
        
end
end

end

function bisection(f, a, b, tol)
    
    if sign(f(a)) == sign(f(b))
        error("function has the same sign at given endpoints")
    end

    mid = (a + b)/2

    while abs(f(mid)) > tol

        sign(f(mid)) == sign(f(a)) ? a=mid : b=mid
            
        mid = (a + b)/2

    end

    return mid
    
end

####### SHEL CROSSING


function delta0(x0)
Mdelta=delta
Mgamma=gamma
Mrho=rho0
G=1
ret=(1//5 * G * Mdelta * Mrho * sqrt(pi) * Mgamma ^ 2 * x0 ^ -4 * (G * Mdelta * Mrho * Mgamma ^ 2 * x0 ^ -3 * (-2 * x0 * exp(-1//50 * x0 ^ 2) + 5 * sqrt(2) * sqrt(pi) * erf(1//10 * x0 * sqrt(2)))) ^ (-1//2) * (1 + 100 * pi * G * Mdelta * Mrho * Mgamma ^ 2 * x0 ^ -3 * (2 * x0 * exp(-1//50 * x0 ^ 2) + -5 * sqrt(2) * sqrt(pi) * erf(1//10 * x0 * sqrt(2)))) ^( -1//2) * (-2 * x0 * (75 + x0 ^ 2) + 375 * sqrt(2) * sqrt(pi) * erf(1//10 * x0 * sqrt(2)) * exp(1//50 * x0 ^ 2)) * exp(-1//50 * x0 ^ 2))
return ret
end


function deltaNUM(l1,x0)
function rowdelta(du, u, p, l)
du[1]=-2*sin(2*beta(l, Beta0(x0)))*u[1]-x(l, x0)*cos(2*beta(l, Beta0(x0)))*u[1]^2
end
u0=[delta0(x0)]
lspan=(0,150 )



condition(u,t,integrator) = u[1] - 1e9 # Is zero when u[3] = 10
affect!(integrator) = terminate!(integrator)
cb = ContinuousCallback(condition,affect!)    
    

prob=ODEProblem(rowdelta,u0, lspan,callback = cb, reltol=1e-4,abstol=1e-4 )
sol1=solve(prob)

return sol1(l1)[1]
end


function lamshell(x0)

function test(l1)
return deltaNUM(l1,x0)-1e8
end

return find_zero(test,(0,1000) )[1]
end

return ret
end
